Date: 0/0/1843
Source: Travels in NZ
Author: DIEFFENBACH
Vol / Page: 1/46
Edition:
Quote: During the six remaining months of the year the ships cruising in the `whaling-ground' fall in with many whales. This whaling-ground extends from the Chatham Islands to the eastward of the northern island of New Zealand, and from thence to Norfolk Island. It is curious that the whalers assert that this whaling-ground is nothing but a shoal, although I am not aware that soundings have ever been obtained.
